In this proclamation, President Donald Trump officially recognizes Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and announces the relocation of the United States Embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem. He states that this decision is in line with the will of Congress and the United States' commitment to facilitating a lasting peace agreement. The proclamation emphasizes that the United States takes no position on the final status issues and the specific boundaries of Israeli sovereignty in Jerusalem will be subject to negotiations between the parties involved. President Trump also reaffirms the United States' support for the status quo at Jerusalem's holy sites and expresses hope for peace in the region.